result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathan E. Cabral was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(3rd+ w/in3Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Huber privileges and Good Time Credit granted.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

Authenticated Warrant had not yet been rec'd by WCSD

Case Recalled @ 3:20 PM: Defendant Jonathan E. Cabral in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def failed to appear earlier this morning and a warrant had been issued.  Court questions Def as to status of counsel with SPD.  Def states he was found not eligible for SPD services.  Court notes Def had previously spoken with the State on resolution.  Def requests to speak with the State further without counsel.  Off Record for Def to speak with the DA.  Back of Record @ 3:25 PM:   Per DA:  In reality a 5th offense exists and offer again extended.  State will argue for 15 days WCJ and Costs.  Def confirms he will accept resolution.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea:  No DL 3 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Statement by Def:   Yes - requests Huber.  The Court:  Accepts resolution and imposes 15 days WCJ, Report 11/1/2015 @ 8:00 PM - Huber, GT and No TS credit, Costs - 60 DTP or PP.  DNA Sample and Surcharge Assessed.  Expungement process thru the DOJ explained of DNA record.  Appeal Rights Given.  Warrant Withdrawn by the Court - Bond ordered forfeited.

9:57 am case called. Defendant Jonathan E. Cabral not in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court issues warrant based on non-appearance-State of Wisconsin. Court orders cash bond forfeited.
No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Case Called @ 3:20 PM: Defendant Jonathan E. Cabral in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wants counsel.  Def requests to speak to the DA on his own without counsel.  Def states he is moving to Chicago very soon.  Off Record for Def to speak with DA.  Back of Record @ 3:30 pm:  Def wishes to contact SPD.  NGP entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for October 20, 2015 at 09:30 am.
